INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (5,1,'2026-07-01 15:14:45','2026-07-01 15:14:45','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you''ve been anywhere near K-pop-adjacent or gacha-game corners of the internet in the past couple of weeks, you''ve probably seen the name "Valko" everywhere — and not because players are excited about him anymore.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Who Was Valko?</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Valko was set to be the sixth love interest in <em>Love and Deepspace</em>, the hugely popular otome/gacha mobile game from developer Infold Games (Papergames). He was revealed as a tall, golden-eyed werewolf character — complete with wolf ears and tail — and was originally scheduled to launch with the game''s Version 6.0 update on July 9, 2026.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>His reveal initially generated a lot of excitement, especially among fans who wanted a new love interest with a more overtly "beast" archetype. But the excitement didn''t last long.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class="wp-block-heading">What Went Wrong</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The controversy unfolded on two fronts:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Promotional messaging.</strong> Some of the marketing copy for Valko used language and imagery that a portion of the Chinese player base felt romanticized concepts like home intrusion and stalking — read by some as uncomfortably close to normalizing invasive, non-consensual scenarios rather than simple werewolf theming.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Historical sensitivity.</strong> Separately, players connected certain in-game asset codes and placeholder data tied to Valko with references to a historically painful and sensitive chapter of the Sino-Japanese conflict. That association proved deeply upsetting to many players and added a much heavier dimension to the backlash than a typical character-design complaint.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The fallout was significant: the developer reportedly lost around a million followers on Chinese social media, fans staged protests outside the company''s Shanghai headquarters, and the game''s roadmap took a direct hit.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class="wp-block-heading">The Global Fanbase Pushed Back Too — Just in the Other Direction</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Here''s where it gets messier: while the backlash was concentrated among Chinese players, a large portion of the <em>global</em> fanbase actually liked Valko and didn''t want him cancelled. Petitions calling for his release reportedly gathered more than 80,000 signatures, and the hashtag associated with him trended worldwide on X.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>That created a genuine divide in the community — between players who saw the character as harmful and those who felt a vocal segment was dictating content decisions for the entire global playerbase.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class="wp-block-heading">The Outcome</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>On June 30, 2026, Infold Games officially confirmed Valko''s permanent cancellation. In their statement, the company apologized for the distress caused and said the game would not introduce any further new love interests going forward — making the already-released Caleb the final addition to the roster.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Why It Resonated Beyond the Game</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>What makes this story stick isn''t just "a character got cancelled." It''s a case study in how a single character reveal can surface much bigger tensions: regional versus global audience priorities, how sensitive it can be to gamify serious historical events, and how quickly live-service games can be forced to reverse major content decisions once backlash reaches a critical mass.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For a game built almost entirely around its cast of love interests, permanently freezing the roster is a pretty dramatic move — and it''s likely to shape how <em>Love and Deepspace</em>, and other live-service romance games, approach new character reveals going forward.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Valko and the Love and Deepspace Controversy','','publish','open','open','','valko-and-the-love-and-deepspace-controversy-explained','','','2026-07-03 01:13:30','2026-07-03 01:13:30','',0,'http://localhost:8881/?p=5',0,'post','',0);
