INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (18,1,'2026-07-02 00:28:13','2026-07-02 00:28:13','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Built a multi-client chat server and static web server from scratch in C, using fork() and socket programming to handle concurrent connections. The chat server supports usernames, timestamps, and file-based logging for real-time communication. Load-tested with Apache Benchmark, the web server handled 1,000 HTTP requests across 10 parallel connections in just 0.322 seconds with zero failures — and the results were used to analyze fork()''s scalability limits compared to threading and event-driven approaches.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Fork-Based Multi-Client Server (C)','','publish','closed','closed','','fork-based-multi-client-server-c','','','2026-07-02 00:28:13','2026-07-02 00:28:13','',0,'http://localhost:8881/?post_type=project&#038;p=18',0,'project','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (19,1,'2026-07-02 22:57:10','2026-07-02 22:57:10','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Built an interactive 2D program in Godot (C#) visualizing Yogyakarta''s cultural elements, traditional houses and batik motifs, rendered entirely from primitive shapes (lines, rectangles, trapezoids, triangles, circles, ellipses) using the midpoint circle and polygon algorithms. Developed four versions: static, animated, colored animation, and a fully interactive mode where users control animation speed, scale objects up or down, select which object to resize, and toggle an on-screen guide. Solo developer, designed the base classes, implemented shape-generation algorithms, applied transformation matrices for animation and interaction, and built the object-selection and keyboard controls.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Yogyakarta Culture: Interactive 2D Graphics Program','','publish','closed','closed','','yogyakarta-culture-interactive-2d-graphics-program','','','2026-07-02 22:57:10','2026-07-02 22:57:10','',0,'http://localhost:8881/?post_type=project&#038;p=19',0,'project','',0);
